{"ts":1779811467744,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I see you have a cron job set up to monitor UTR availability on the Ubiquiti store. This job runs a bash script that:\n\n1. Checks the UTR product page at `https://store.ui.com/us/en/category/wifi-special-devices/products/utr`\n2. Uses `html2text` to convert the HTML to readable text\n3. Looks for \"Add to Cart\" or \"Sold Out\" text\n4. Compares the current status with a previous state stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.utr-state`\n5. Sends a notification when the status changes (available → sold out or sold out → available)\n\nThe cron job ID is `587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7` and it's currently active.\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Check the current status of the UTR availability?\n- Modify the cron job schedule or behavior?\n- View the current state file to see the last known status?\n- Test the script to make sure it's working correctly?\n- Set up additional monitoring or notifications?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"3c03b86b-5161-4453-a94a-5cd9dae6aa8f","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:3c03b86b-5161-4453-a94a-5cd9dae6aa8f","runAtMs":1779811451267,"durationMs":16467,"nextRunAtMs":1779815051246,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":329,"output_tokens":555,"total_tokens":329}}
