{"ts":1779854692878,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"Based on the cron job history, here's what I found:\n\n**Current Status:**\n- The job is enabled and configured to run hourly (0 * * * * in America/Los_Angeles timezone)\n- **Last run failed** at 2026-05-27 04:04 UTC with a generic error\n- **Previous 8 runs succeeded** — all showing UTR status as \"Sold Out\" with no changes\n\n**What's Working:**\n- State tracking is functioning — the job successfully compares current vs. previous availability\n- The curl + html2text fetch is working in successful runs\n- No notifications are being sent (delivery mode is \"none\"), which is correct since status hasn't changed\n\n**The Issue:**\nThe most recent run errored out, but I can't access the detailed error logs from outside the cron job's execution context. The error appears to be transient since previous runs succeeded.\n\n**Next Steps:**\nThe job should recover on the next scheduled run (hourly). If you want to:\n- **See detailed error logs** — I'd need to spawn a sub-agent to investigate\n- **Enable notifications** — set delivery mode to announce/webhook so you get alerted when it becomes available\n- **Adjust the schedule** — change from hourly to a different interval\n- **Verify it's working** — I can check the state file to see what was last recorded\n\nWhat would be most helpful?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"a549ff2a-15b7-45d5-adae-06d2a211fcff","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:a549ff2a-15b7-45d5-adae-06d2a211fcff","runAtMs":1779854651266,"durationMs":41589,"nextRunAtMs":1779858251246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":1627,"output_tokens":1800,"total_tokens":383}}
