{"ts":1779901472981,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"**UTR Availability Monitor Status Summary**\n\nYour monitor is running smoothly. Here's what I found:\n\n**Current State:**\n- **Device Status:** Sold Out (unchanged since May 16)\n- **Last Check:** ~50 minutes ago — successful\n- **Next Check:** Scheduled for top of the next hour\n- **Model:** Correctly configured for haiku-4.5 ✓\n\n**Recent History:**\n- 30 consecutive successful runs tracking the device as sold out\n- A few timeout errors earlier (May 26, 8:30–9:30 AM PT), but the job recovered\n- One run incorrectly used deepseek-3.2 (shouldn't happen with current config)\n- State tracking is working — comparing current vs. previous availability correctly\n\n**One Gap:**\nDelivery mode is set to `none`, so even when the device becomes available, you won't receive a notification. You'd only know by checking the job history manually.\n\n**What would be useful?**\n\n1. **Enable notifications** — Set delivery to announce/webhook so you get alerted the moment it's back in stock (which channel — email, Slack, Discord, or system message?)\n2. **Adjust frequency** — Change from hourly to more/less frequent checks\n3. **Manually trigger a check now** — Verify it's working in real-time\n4. **Leave it as-is** — Keep monitoring silently in the background\n\nWhat's your preference?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"e97d1706-6ccb-4ddc-b819-293b1cd3e1dc","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:e97d1706-6ccb-4ddc-b819-293b1cd3e1dc","runAtMs":1779901451283,"durationMs":21688,"nextRunAtMs":1779905051246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":561,"output_tokens":958,"total_tokens":300}}
