{"ts":1779937495659,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"The availability check is complete. However, I should note that the cron job has `delivery.mode: \"none\"`, which is why it's failing to send notifications when the state changes.\n\nTo fix this, the cron job configuration needs to be updated to enable notifications. Since I'm running as an isolated agent spawned by the job, I can't modify the job itself—that requires the parent session to update it.\n\n**What needs to happen:**\nThe cron job should be updated to set:\n- `delivery.mode: \"announce\"` \n- `delivery.channel: \"<your-notification-channel>\"` (e.g., \"dj-notifications\" or similar)\n\nThis will allow the job to send notifications when UTR availability changes from available → sold out or vice versa.\n\nWould you like me to provide the exact cron update command, or do you have access to update the job configuration directly?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"87241887-90a5-4c62-9aee-53a5a3b1dfd7","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:87241887-90a5-4c62-9aee-53a5a3b1dfd7","runAtMs":1779937451260,"durationMs":44392,"nextRunAtMs":1779941051246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":2668,"output_tokens":1957,"total_tokens":502}}
