{"ts":1779951868495,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I can see the issue. Your UTR monitor is **working correctly** — it detected that the device became **available** (status changed from Sold Out → Available) — but the last two runs failed because **delivery mode is set to `none`**, so it can't send notifications.\n\nHere's what happened:\n\n**Recent Run Summary:**\n- ✅ May 27, 5:04 AM UTC: Device status changed **Sold Out → Available** (detected successfully)\n- ❌ Notification failed to send (delivery.mode = \"none\")\n- ✅ May 27, 3:04 AM UTC: Same state change detected, same delivery failure\n- ✅ Earlier runs: Device remained Sold Out, no changes\n\n**The Fix:**\n\nI can update the cron job to enable notifications. Which would you prefer?\n\n1. **System message** — Announce to the current session when availability changes\n2. **Email** — Send to a specific email address\n3. **Slack/Discord** — Send to a channel (provide the webhook URL or channel ID)\n4. **Just fix the error** — Enable announce mode to the default channel\n\nWhich notification method works best for you?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"a3fe8e79-3b5f-4ca2-b588-70b03f6f3033","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:a3fe8e79-3b5f-4ca2-b588-70b03f6f3033","runAtMs":1779951851293,"durationMs":17194,"nextRunAtMs":1779955451246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":561,"output_tokens":818,"total_tokens":300}}
