{"ts":1779959068923,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"Your UTR Availability Monitor is **active and working correctly**. Here's the current status:\n\n**Latest Check (May 28, 2:04 AM PT):**\n- Status: **Available** (contains \"Add to Cart\")\n- Previous state: **Available**\n- Change detected: No\n- Notification sent: No (no state change)\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\nThe device **became available** at some point (detected in earlier runs around May 27, 5:04 AM UTC), but since then it's remained available with no further changes. The monitor is tracking state properly.\n\n**The Gap:**\nYour cron job has `delivery.mode: \"none\"`, which means:\n- ✓ State tracking works perfectly\n- ✓ Change detection works\n- ✗ But notifications aren't being sent when availability changes\n\n**What I can do:**\n\n1. **Enable notifications** — Update the cron job to send alerts when availability changes. Which channel would you prefer?\n   - System message (announce to your session)\n   - Email\n   - Slack/Discord webhook\n   - Other\n\n2. **Manually trigger a check now** — Verify the monitor is working in real-time\n\n3. **Adjust the schedule** — Change from hourly to a different interval\n\n4. **Leave it as-is** — Keep monitoring silently (you can always check the job history manually)\n\nWhat would be most useful?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"16665d22-8b3a-4892-b932-50b8185cea8b","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:16665d22-8b3a-4892-b932-50b8185cea8b","runAtMs":1779959051296,"durationMs":17612,"nextRunAtMs":1779962651246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":561,"output_tokens":852,"total_tokens":300}}
