{"ts":1780196703414,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"**UTR Availability Monitor Status Summary**\n\nThe cron job is mostly working but hit an error on the most recent run (May 31 at 8:04 PM PDT). Here's what I found:\n\n**Current State:**\n- **Device Status:** Sold Out (consistent since May 11, 2026)\n- **Last Successful Check:** May 30 at 6:04 PM PDT — confirmed Sold Out\n- **Most Recent Run:** May 31 at 8:04 PM PDT — **ERROR** (⚠️ ⏰ Cron failed)\n- **Schedule:** Hourly at top of hour with 5-minute stagger\n- **Model:** Correctly configured for haiku-4.5 ✓\n\n**Issues Identified:**\n1. **Recent error** — The job failed on the last run; unclear why from the diagnostics\n2. **No notifications** — `delivery.mode` is set to `\"none\"`, so even if availability changes, you won't be alerted\n3. **Intermittent failures** — I see occasional \"Message failed\" errors in the history, suggesting notification delivery issues when enabled\n\n**What I can do:**\n1. **Investigate the error** — Check if it's a transient issue or something systemic\n2. **Enable notifications** — Configure the job to alert you when status changes (email, Slack, Discord, or system message)\n3. **Adjust the schedule** — Change frequency if needed\n4. **Run a manual check now** — Verify the monitoring logic is still working\n\nWhat would be most helpful?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"814b38ba-41b0-446a-8bc6-2c27c21b9c01","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:814b38ba-41b0-446a-8bc6-2c27c21b9c01","runAtMs":1780196651261,"durationMs":52144,"nextRunAtMs":1780200251246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":3620,"output_tokens":2829,"total_tokens":528}}
