{"ts":1780254265863,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"**UTR Availability Monitor Status**\n\nThe cron job is running smoothly. Here's the current state:\n\n**Latest Run (May 31, 12:04 PM):**\n- Status: ✓ OK\n- Device: **Sold Out** (no change from previous check)\n- Next run: May 31, 1:04 PM\n\n**Job Health:**\n- Enabled: Yes\n- Schedule: Hourly at top of hour + 5-min stagger\n- Model: haiku-4.5 ✓\n- Consecutive errors: 0\n- Uptime: Consistent since May 11 (20 days of monitoring)\n\n**Key Issue:**\nNotifications are disabled (`delivery.mode: \"none\"`). If the UTR becomes available, you won't be alerted—you'd only know by checking the cron history manually.\n\n**What I can do:**\n\n1. **Enable notifications** — Set up alerts when availability changes (email, Slack, Discord, or system message)\n2. **Run a manual check now** — Verify the current status immediately\n3. **Investigate intermittent errors** — Some runs show \"Message failed\" or \"Cron failed\" errors; I can diagnose these\n4. **Adjust the schedule** — Change frequency if hourly is too often/infrequent\n\nWhich would be most useful?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"d20c3d89-ce23-4845-ba58-9b3f25ce92e5","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:d20c3d89-ce23-4845-ba58-9b3f25ce92e5","runAtMs":1780254251266,"durationMs":14589,"nextRunAtMs":1780257851246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":554,"output_tokens":849,"total_tokens":293}}
