{"ts":1780333527739,"jobId":"587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I'm hitting a constraint: cron jobs can only be modified from within their own execution context, not from the main session. The existing job is failing because it's running in isolation without persistent state.\n\nHere's what I've set up so far:\n- Created a state file at `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/.utr-state.json` to track availability\n- Created a helper script at `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/check-utr-availability.sh` for the check logic\n\nThe real fix needs to happen from within the cron job itself. The job needs to:\n1. Read the state file before checking\n2. Fetch the page and parse the status\n3. Compare with the previous status\n4. Send a notification if it changed\n5. Write the new state back\n\nSince I can't modify the cron job from here, you have two options:\n\n**Option A:** Let the cron job run on its next scheduled time (next hour), and it will need to be debugged from within its isolated run to see what's actually failing.\n\n**Option B:** I can spawn a one-time isolated agent right now to perform the check with proper state handling, which would validate the approach works before we worry about the scheduled job.\n\nWhich would you prefer?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"62a6ab58-1140-47cd-8a3f-46a90d764e3b","sessionKey":"agent:main:cron:587736e6-c589-4867-9b1e-ac921b4e5fa7:run:62a6ab58-1140-47cd-8a3f-46a90d764e3b","runAtMs":1780333451278,"durationMs":76444,"nextRunAtMs":1780337051246,"model":"claude-haiku-4.5","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":4071,"output_tokens":3335,"total_tokens":629}}
